<!-- ALTERNATIVE #2 - This is just like ALTERNATIVE #1, except we have introduced finer-grained typing in the METS structMap. 
      The div TYPE attribute is used to put more meaning into each node in the hierarchy.  A div TYPE explicitly asserts the kind of 
      Fedora component the div should be mapped to (i.e., FedoraObject, FedoraDatastream), and also the kind of NARA entity 
      the div represents (e.g., aggregateTemplate, documentTemplate, recordContent, recordMetadata).  
      The div structure is deeper than the one presented in ALTERNATIVE #1 in that there is a unique div parent for each 
      individual fptr element to provide explicit fine-grained typing of every piece of content or metadata.  -->
